This product is a C# port of and derivative work of Philter-Lite,
originally developed by the UCSF Department of Pediatrics:

    Philter-Lite
    https://github.com/UCSF-Pediatrics/philter-lite
    BSD 3-Clause License
    Copyright (c) UCSF Department of Pediatrics

The base filter pipeline configuration (`philter_delta.json`) and the
lookup sets in `Configuration/sets/` are derived from the upstream
Philter-Lite distribution. Upstream BSD-3 attribution applies to those
artifacts; modifications and additions ship under this project's BSD-3
license alongside.

The C# filter engine implementation, configuration loader, sidecar
mechanism, and POS tagger integrations are original work.

---

The Philter.NET.PerceptronTagger package embeds and ports the NLTK averaged
perceptron part-of-speech tagger:

    Averaged Perceptron Tagger
    Copyright 2013 Matthew Honnibal
    NLTK port / modifications Copyright 2015 The NLTK Project
    MIT License

    The C# inference port (AveragedPerceptron.cs, PerceptronPosTagger.cs) is
    derived from nltk/tag/perceptron.py. The embedded model data
    (averaged_perceptron_tagger_eng.{weights,tagdict,classes}.json) is the
    pretrained English model distributed by the NLTK Data project under the
    MIT License (per the NLTK data index). Permission notice retained per MIT.

